# IntuAIive - Video Summarization App

IntuAIive is a full-stack web application that summarizes YouTube videos or uploaded audio/video files (M4A/MP4) into concise bullet points with downloadable audio. Built as a portfolio project to showcase full-stack development skills.

## Features
- **Summarization**: Transcribes audio using AssemblyAI and summarizes into 3 bullet points using Ollama, focusing on actions and decisions.
- **Authentication**: Secure Google sign-in via Firebase.
- **Real-Time Updates**: Socket.IO provides live progress updates during processing (download, conversion, upload, transcription, summarization).
- **Storage**: Audio files are stored on AWS S3 with immediate temp file cleanup.
- **UI**: Sleek cosmic-themed React frontend with Tailwind CSS and custom animations.
- **Database**: SQLite stores meeting summaries (S3 URL, transcript, bullets).

## Tech Stack
- **Frontend**: React, Tailwind CSS (CDN), React Router, Firebase Authentication
- **Backend**: Node.js, Express, Socket.IO, SQLite, AWS S3
- **APIs**: AssemblyAI (transcription), Ollama (summarization), youtube-dl-exec (YouTube downloads)
- **Tools**: Fluent-FFmpeg (video-to-audio conversion), Multer (file uploads)

## Demo
Watch the demo video: [IntuAIive Demo](https://youtu.be/mHOy547Dm94)

## Setup
1. Clone the repo: `git clone https://github.com/your-username/summary-project.git`
2. Install dependencies: `npm install` (root) and `cd frontend && npm install`
3. Set up environment variables in `.env` (root) and `frontend/.env`
4. Run the app: `npm start`
5. Open `http://localhost:3000`

